OL,6,FBut in the 1970s and 80s, the biggest
OL,7,Fdanger was INSIDE the school grounds,
OL,8,Fas blood treatments, meant to improve
OL,9,Ftheir lives, began to infect them.
OL,11,FIn total 122 boys contracted HIV or
OL,12,FHepatitis C, some of them, both.
OL,14,FFewer than 20 survive.
OL,16,FReturning to the school chapel, they
OL,17,Fspoke of the trauma of losing
OL,18,Fclassmates and being told they'd been
OL,19,Finfected with deadly diseases.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/18
