OL,6,F"The impact was a bomb. We were given
OL,7,Ftwo years to live - we were going to
OL,8,Fdie, and most of us did, " says Ade
OL,9,FGoodyear, 50, from Portsmouth, who was
OL,10,Fsent to the college at the age of 10.
OL,12,FA haemophiliac, he was one of those
OL,13,Finfected at the school between 1974
OL,14,Fand 1987, after being given a drug
OL,15,Fcontaminated with HIV and viral
OL,16,Fhepatitis.
OL,18,FSince then, at least 72 have died,
OL,19,Fwhile survivors have had to live with
OL,20,Fdecades of ill-health, stigma and
OL,21,Flittle or no support.
