OL,6,FFor boys like Ade, arriving at
OL,7,FTreloars was a godsend. He had
OL,8,Fpreviously been bullied, his arm had
OL,9,Fbeen broken by a boy "who wanted to
OL,10,Fsee what happened when you hit a
OL,11,Fhaemophiliac."
OL,13,FHe was used to seeing "home, hospital,
OL,14,Fa sofa and not much more" but at
OL,15,FTreloars he made friends, was free to
OL,16,Frun around, play football and get an
OL,17,Feducation.
