OL,6,FSteve Nicholls, 54, agrees: "The bonds
OL,7,Fand the friendships that were formed
OL,8,Fhere were more than the normal friends
OL,9,Fand relationships. We became like
OL,10,Fblood brothers and I think that's how
OL,11,Fwe all consider ourselves"
OL,13,FSteve Nicholls and Gary Webster
OL,14,Fdescribe the bonds forged at Treloars
OL,16,FSteve, from Farnham, went to Treloars
OL,17,Fin 1976 when he was eight. He gave
OL,18,Fevidence at the beginning of the
OL,19,Fenquiry and describes how the arrival
OL,20,Fof Factor VIII initially transformed
OL,21,Ftheir lives for the better:
