OL,6,FAs early as 1975 boys at Treloars
OL,7,Fbegan to fall ill, initially with
OL,8,Fhepatitis. Former pupils remember boys
OL,9,Fturning yellow, and being segregated
OL,10,Ffrom other students. But by the early
OL,11,F1980s, with the stigma of AIDS at its
OL,12,Fhighest- they began to receive
OL,13,Fdevastating news that they were
OL,14,Finfected with not only hepatitis, but
OL,15,FHIV too.
OL,17,FLee Moorey, 48, remembers that moment
OL,18,Fvividly: "I came here when I was 12
OL,19,Fyears old. Two years later, I was told
OL,20,FI had only two years to live"
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/18
