OL,6,F"We made a pledge then that we'll see
OL,7,Fthis through" says Steve. "If there's
OL,8,Fever anyone around, we'll find out and
OL,9,Fget to the truth. That's why we're
OL,10,Fhere today."
OL,12,FGary Webster, 56, from Eastleigh,
OL,13,Fagrees. He was sent to the school in
OL,14,F1975, one of the first haemophiliacs
OL,15,Fto attend: "It's only when we're all
OL,16,Ftogether that we can truly be
OL,17,Fourselves" he says. "We all just
OL,18,Funderstand what each of us has been
OL,19,Fthrough, we've shared the pain, the
OL,20,Fdisappointments, the anger, both at
OL,21,Fschool and since"
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G11/18
