OL,6,FThey've been well-supported by
OL,7,FTreloars, which remains a pioneering
OL,8,Fand outstanding school- windows in the
OL,9,Fchapel commemorate the pupils they
OL,10,Flost, and they have never shied away
OL,11,Ffrom what is a tragic part of their
OL,12,Fpast.
OL,14,FBut some former pupils find it
OL,15,Fimpossible to forgive the school's
OL,16,Frole in the scandal, believing they
OL,17,Fshould have been much more protective
OL,18,Fof their students.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G13/18
